@page "/legal/privacy"
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]

<h1 class="h3 mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>
<p class="text-body-secondary small">Last updated: @DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("MMMM d, yyyy")</p>

<p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>WebRomani</strong> collects, uses, and protects your information when you use our site.
</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">Information we collect</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Account data (username, email).</li>
    <li>Content you submit (novels, chapters, reviews).</li>
    <li>Usage data (page views, read counts), collected in aggregate.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">How we use information</h2>
<ul>
    <li>To provide core features (reading, bookmarking, reviewing).</li>
    <li>To improve performance, discoverability, and user experience.</li>
    <li>To keep the service secure and prevent abuse.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">Cookies</h2>
<p>
    We use essential cookies for authentication and session management. You can control cookies via your browser settings.
</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">Data retention</h2>
<p>
    We retain account and content data while your account is active. You may request deletion of your account and associated content where feasible.
</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">Third parties</h2>
<p>
    We do not sell your personal data. Limited data may be processed by infrastructure/service providers strictly to operate the site.
</p>

<h2 class="h5 mt-4">Contact</h2>
<p>
    Questions? Email us at <a href="mailto:hello@example.com">hello@example.com</a>.
</p>
